post: {'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Under legalisation, self-injection as a route of administration may be reduced, as safer alternatives become available.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "That's exactly what we have today. So all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'US states that have legalised marijuana have seen a lot of benefits.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Personal autonomy](https://www.law.cornell.edu/wex/personal_autonomy) is not a fundamental right in the US constitution.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The first [anti-cocaine laws](http://www.drugpolicy.org/issues/brief-history-drug-war) in the early 1900s were directed at black men in the South.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Incarceration does not treat addiction; the money spent on incarcerated non-violent drug offenders could be instead used to fund addiction treatment.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many poor people use drugs as a temporary escape from poverty [\\(Scottish Drugs Forum, p. 12\\)](http://www.dldocs.stir.ac.uk/documents/drugpovertylitrev.pdf). Criminalization of this behavior does not help them.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Removing some of these constraints through the legalisation of drugs could make studies more successful.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "In a truly free society self regulation should be our privilege. You are free to not use drugs, and you should be just as free to use them. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This could lead individuals into a false sense of safety when it comes to drug use.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The only way to know if the related compound acts the same is by doing the research that was banned in the first place. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalization runs the danger of increased drug use that could impair people from doing jobs safely, making work places more dangerous.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Due to abundance and normalization, people could enjoy other drugs like the enjoy a glass of wine. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the US, as of 2018 there are roughly [235,000](https://www.prisonpolicy.org/reports/pie2018.html) inmates behind bars for drug-related crimes. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Without help some conditions could [worsen](https://deserthopetreatment.com/co-occurring-disorders/going-untreated/) to the point where they're a danger to others. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This is an appeal to nature fallacy. Nature is not the word on what ought to be done with its products.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Currently medical professionals can and do discriminate against those who use substances simply because they're illegal. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug prohibition might be inspired by some kind of racism but abandoning it would not necessarily mean an improvement of the situation for those incarcerated or addicted to drugs. There are still many other systematic racial issues unrelated to drug prohibition.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Sobriety may be required for the optimal exercise of rational moral agency; however, it is not required for the generell exercise of rational moral agency. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Colorado has seen a "[slight increase](https://www.colorado.gov/pacific/cdphe/marijuana-use-2017)" in the number of adult marijuana users in the period 2014-2017 following legalisation. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "It can also cause users to mix alcohol with other drugs, which [endangers users' health](https://www.northpointwashington.com/blog/dangers-mixing-alcohol-drugs/) even more."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Coming from families with unstable backgrounds alone is associated with withdrawal from societal life. It might be the cause of both the withdrawal and the drug use. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help contain the dangerous drug cartels. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The black market businesses won't be able to invest in productivity-increasing \\(especially immovable\\) capital, as the threat of being caught discourages such investments. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'People would prefer less addicting drugs, so as to lessen the risk of taking them. This would lead to companies to develop less addictive drugs as well.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Through legalising drugs within a finite border, the criminal economic chain could be controlled inside that border only.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The "[27 club](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/27_Club)" is an infamous list of artists who died from overdosing on drugs at the age of 27. That\'s why drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If government regulations lead to drugs being expensive, it is possible people will still try to access cheaper drugs on a black market and these drugs may still be dangerous or of poor quality. I think legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Mushrooms and MDMA](http://www.ias.org.uk/uploads/pdf/News%20stories/dnutt-lancet-011110.pdf) have been classed safer than tobacco and alcohol. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This could lead individuals into a false sense of safety when it comes to drug use.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Several 'great' artists have died from an overdose on drugs and thus actually causing negative contributions to human culture as the world is deprived of their 'artwork'."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The [global financial crisis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Financial_crisis_of_2007%E2%80%932008) was caused by big companies acting with only their profits in mind, and the detrimental effects are still felt today. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Due to abundance and normalization, people could enjoy other drugs like the enjoy a glass of wine. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The pharmaceutical industry is far less dangerous or violent than the alternative of drug cartels. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If drugs other than alcohol were legalized, alcohol sales would plummet, and a lot of jobs in the alcohol industry would disappear.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'While neither seems acceptable, most would rather face prejudice than prison. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Young people could use fake IDs to buy drugs, the same way they currently do with alcohol and cigarettes.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In 2018, the consumption patterns of most US citizens who used illicit drugs were [unproblematic](https://filtermag.org/2018/09/25/the-invisible-majority-people-whose-drug-use-is-not-problematic/). I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The drug industry, like alcohol and tobacco, can be heavily taxed, generating high revenues. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The responsible use of drugs for recreational purposes does not harm others and therefore can not be considered immoral. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Incarceration does not treat addiction; the money spent on incarcerated non-violent drug offenders could be instead used to fund addiction treatment.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is undeniable; however, the same is true whether drugs are legal or not. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Entheogenic drugs](https://maps.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=5468), such as psychedelics, have been used throughout human history for many benefits in evolutionary growth and cognitive development.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Producers and distributors are not able to control how consumers use their products. Therefore, legalising the sale and possession of drugs necessarily would allow for this kind of abuse to increase easily despite the illegality of forcing another person to ingest them.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'When the government legalizes something, it \\(unintentionally\\) sends the message that the substance is acceptable and a legitimate form of recreation. This may encourage people to become involved in drug taking.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Criminals will face competition from legal growers with lower shipping costs, which will drive prices down.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The same applies to already legal alcohol. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug use correlates negatively with socially-responsible behavior. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There has been [no scientific consensus](https://newatlas.com/study-effects-ecstasy/10995/) on the long-term effects of ecstasy use.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There are often structurally similar legal compounds which can be researched instead of the illegal variation. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help contain the dangerous drug cartels. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'High taxes may ensure that a black market for drugs remains with all the dangers it already has. So drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Other factors contribute to the opioid crisis significantly more than the legality of currently prescribed opioids. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Job security in an immoral industry should not be an argument for maintaining the status quo.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Using a fake ID in a legal establishment implies much more work and risk than just buying from the unregulated black market.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Many Canadian cigarettes are [smuggled back](https://www.publicsafety.gc.ca/cnt/rsrcs/pblctns/archive-stts-cntrbnd-tbcc/index-en.aspx) into Canada.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legal companies would be able to take over the drugs-related sector from illegal criminal organisations. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Tracing a car owner by his license plate after causing a severe accident with people killed does not undo the accident either. But it creates a moral barrier for people, so they think twice before doing such a hit and run. Same goes for traceable drugs. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Since drug addicts have an impaired sense of \\(rational\\) judgement, drug addiction is detrimental to personal autonomy.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "In Uruguay, possession of drugs for personal use [is legal](https://www.tni.org/es/node/16660). That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Criminals will have to either adapt or lose the income that prevents their other crimes from catching up with them.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "A parent's drugs addiction can cause a child to suffer emotional harm and a lack of future stability as it can reduce the parent's life expectancy, causing them to die young. So drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The Netherlands' comparably liberal [drug policy](https://www.opensocietyfoundations.org/voices/safe-and-effective-drug-policy-look-dutch) has generated positive outcomes."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug use negatively affects job performance.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If an individual is already addicted, that would indicate they already have regular access to the drug.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There is no way to determine in advance what the additional resources/revenue will be used for by the government. It may not be earmarked for harm reduction. So drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs being legal shifts the focus of the police from investigating crimes where individuals damaged others instead of themselves. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The issue with these drugs is that it's possible for someone to ingest it unknowingly, after someone dropped them in their drink etc. I think all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Without help some conditions could [worsen](https://deserthopetreatment.com/co-occurring-disorders/going-untreated/) to the point where they're a danger to others. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The Federal Government \\(US\\) has no constitutional authority to regulate what citizens choose to put in their bodies. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[The Controlled Substances Act](https://www.dea.gov/druginfo/ds.shtml), prohibits Schedule 1 substances \\(such as Cannabis\\), which forces patients to either break the law or use more harmful/addictive substances that are inferior medicine. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This is because the US prison system is [privately owned.](https://smartasset.com/mortgage/the-economics-of-the-american-prison-system) Incentive structures mean that running prisons can only be profitable with high rates of incarceration.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Shooting \\(illegally obtained\\) heroin is like playing Russian roulette every time: if a batch is too strong, over-dosing is likely. That's why all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The "[27 club](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/27_Club)" is an infamous list of artists who died from overdosing on drugs at the age of 27. That\'s why drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'People who want to use drugs are largely already able to get access to them, but can have no assurance about their safety or quality. Government regulations could resolve this problem. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "It's always going to be cheaper to produce a product legally. Legal producers don't have to worry about having their stuff stolen by police and can do all their transactions in the legal market which is much more efficient and cheaper."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'People would prefer less addicting drugs, so as to lessen the risk of taking them. This would lead to companies to develop less addictive drugs as well.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Information about the content of legalized drugs would be easier to find and accurate which would help people make informed and safer choice.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'People may drive under the influence of drugs or make other decisions with public consequences.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Creativity can be stimulated through the use of drugs. Drugs could help us to live in a more creative dynamic society.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legal companies would be able to take over the drugs-related sector from illegal criminal organisations. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The right to bodily integrity protects individuals from [forced labor, slavery or torture](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bodily_integrity).'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "It would likely be 'cooler' because companies can market the drugs like they do with cigarettes and alcohol."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Some drugs are toxic at very low doses. These drugs can rightfully be considered weapons as well as intoxicants.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In India, the mental illness known in the West as [Anomie](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anomie) is cured with the drugs Soma, Amrita, and Ganja plus \\(in a more modern interpretation\\) Peyote and Ayahuasca.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'That correlation is not affected by their legality. So, legalization will not make it worse unless it causes the price to go down. Given the emphasis many put on drug taxes as an argument in favor of legalization, that seems unlikely.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It will create jobs, not only in distribution but also in drug clinics and counseling centers. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalising all drugs may give private companies incentives to advertise/promote the use of those, potentially leading to an increase the overall drug use.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This stress would be reduced if the drugs were legal because it would remove the threat of legal danger to any concerned person.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many drugs that are currently illegal have been and are important social tools.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The illegal consumption of heroin without any satisfactory hygiene conditions [supports](https://www.drugabuse.gov/publications/research-reports/heroin/why-are-heroin-users-special-risk-contracting-hivaids-hepatitis-b-c) the development of HIV.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is only true in the case of people whose drug use either causes them to become dangerous or interferes with their lives. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Taking a more effective approach is not giving up. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Education and information campaigns could be funded by taxes on the drugs themselves. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The risk of unknown purity and poor-quality drugs will be minimized. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalizing all drugs will lead to much larger societal rifts: Drug usage is higher among the poor and socially marginalized, which in turn makes their condition worse.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Using a fake ID in a legal establishment implies much more work and risk than just buying from the unregulated black market.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If state distributed drugs freely as a prescription medicine for registered addicts, it could seriously harm the income from organized crime.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Individuals who seek out "forbidden" activities will still seek that thrill and choose other illegal and possibly more dangerous activities to participate in. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If legalised, drug users could be less likely to leave dangerous paraphernalia \\(broken pipes, syringes, etc.\\) behind in public places as the fear of criminal penalties for the possession of drug paraphernalia would no longer be an issue. This would lessen risk of disease and injury. So all drugs should be legal.'}
